Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Left Ventricular Assist Device (LVAD) Market

The left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the market is growing with a CAGR of 9.6% in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029 and is expected to reach USD 1,957.56 million by 2029. Increasing geriatric population along with rising prevalence of cardiac disease and presence of favorable reimbursement policies among others are acting as driver for the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market growth.

Left ventricular assist device (LVAD) is a pump that we use for patients who have reached end-stage heart failure. Left ventricular assist device is surgically implanted and it’s a battery operated, mechanical pump that helps the left ventricle pump blood to the rest of the blood. LVADs can be used as bridge-to-transplant, destination therapy, bridge-to-candidacy therapy and bridge-to-recovery therapy.

Changing lifestyle triggers the development of cardiovascular diseases which has enhanced the requirement of left ventricular assist device (LVAD) products which improves patient outcomes and allows them to lead a better life hence acts as driver for the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market. The complications and risks associated with LVAD and high cost of LVAD implantation and treatment is expected to hinder the growth of left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market growth. Increase in healthcare expenditure and increase in minimally invasive procedure, thus acts as an opportunity for the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market. Increase in product recall pose a serious safety risk to the public restrict the product manufacturers to earn potential benefit in the market and impacts the overall market size, hence acts as challenge for the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market growth.

