Which are the top companies operating in the Left Ventricular Assist Device (LVAD) market?



The major companies which are dealing in the Left Ventricular Assist Device (LVAD) are Abbott, Evaheart, Inc, Saft (A Subsidiary of TotalEnergies), ABIOMED, Berlin Heart, CorWave SA, Jarvik Heart, Inc.among other domestic players. DBMR analysts understand competitive strengths and provide competitive analysis for each competitor separately.

Many contract and agreement and increasing product approvals initiated by the companies’ worldwide which are also accelerating the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market.

For instance, 

In March 2021, Berlin Heart achieved the CE approval and first implantation of an innovative bridging solution for single-ventricle patients. This innovative bridging therapy was developed to improve the end-organ function and hemodynamics of these patients with univentricular physiology through the support of the sub-pulmonary circulation. This has enhanced credibility of the company in left ventricular assist device market.
In January 2020, Abbott LVAD achieved FDA approval for implantation without open surgery. This approval allowed patients to receive LVAD implantation via lateral thoracotomy. This significant advancement allowed patients to receive life-saving LVAD which has improved overall recovery rate among patients.
Collaboration, product launch, business expansion, award and recognition, joint ventures and other strategies by the market player is enhancing the company footprints in the left ventricular assist device (LVAD) market which also provides the benefit for organization’s profit growth.




